heif

Enum HeifBoxType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<HeifBoxType>
      • heif.HeifBoxType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<HeifBoxType>

    public enum HeifBoxType
extends java.lang.Enum<HeifBoxType>
    Defines all supported HEIF (High Efficiency Image File) box types.

    Each HeifBoxType corresponds to a specific 4-character code used in the ISO Base Media File Format (ISOBMFF) and HEIF/HEIC specifications.

    Boxes are categorized as:

    • HeifBoxType.BoxCategory.ATOMIC – Individual data boxes containing fields
    • HeifBoxType.BoxCategory.CONTAINER – Structural boxes that contain child boxes
    • HeifBoxType.BoxCategory.UNKNOWN – Unknown or un-handled box types

    For official specifications, refer to:

    • ISO/IEC 14496-12:2015 (ISOBMFF)
    • ISO/IEC 23008-12:2017 (HEIF)

    Use fromTypeName(String) or fromTypeBytes(byte[]) to resolve box types at runtime.

      • fromTypeName

        public static HeifBoxType fromTypeName(java.lang.String name)
        Resolves a HeifBoxType from a 4-character string. This uses a pre-populated map for efficient lookup, making it O(1) on average.

      • fromTypeBytes

        public static HeifBoxType fromTypeBytes(byte[] raw)
        Resolves a HeifBoxType from a 4-byte array. Comparison is performed using US-ASCII encoding and a pre-populated map for efficiency. This method is O(1) on average after the initial byte array to string conversion.
        Parameters:
        raw - the 4-byte box identifier
        Returns:
        the corresponding HeifBoxType, or UNKNOWN if it is not recognised
